h3. Original Description 
Long words are being cut off in a PDF export. This causes problems for languages where spaces are uncommon, such as Japanese.

h3. Work around

*Note:* In order to break long words in the PDF export a selector containing the {{word-wrap}} property with a value of {{break-word}} has to be added to the PDF stylesheet:

http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Editing+the+PDF+Stylesheet

For example:
{code}
div {  
    word-wrap: break-word;  
}
{code}

*Steps to reproduce*: Create an issue with a catchy summary and a description with a text with more than 300 characters without a space character in the first 300, then search for the catchy summary. You'll end up with a screenful of stack trace.

com.atlassian.studio.jira.search.SearchUtils.Summarizer.createFragment(String):

{noformat}
private static final int MAX_TEXT_LENGTH = 300;
...
        private Fragment createFragment(String text)
        {
            if (text.length()>MAX_TEXT_LENGTH)
            {
                text = text.substring(0, MAX_TEXT_LENGTH);
                text = text.substring(0,text.lastIndexOf(' '));

            }
            return new Summary.Fragment(text);
        }
{noformat}

if the extracted text doesn't contain a space character you'll see sth. like this:

{noformat}
@400000004f067d9c179a5db4 Caused by: java.lang.StringIndexOutOfBoundsException: String index out of range: -1
@400000004f067d9c179a619c 	at java.lang.String.substring(String.java:1937)
@400000004f067d9c179a6d54 	at com.atlassian.studio.jira.search.SearchUtils$Summarizer.createFragment(SearchUtils.java:424)
{noformat}

As part of this fix, the logic in searchresultfragment.vm should be enhanced to never escape. In this particular case, the #set($descHtml = $action.escapeAndSummarize($match.excerpt, $appInstance)) call should either be refactored (preferred, as in that the fragments should be calculated in the controller and any logic for error handling should be in there) or at least a possible RuntimException should be caught and the a helpful message should be written out for that match/hit instead. E.g. a link to SAC/STAC like on /secure/admin/HelpAndSupport.jspa / com.atlassian.studio.host.common.ThemeProperties.getSupportRequestUrl(HttpServletRequest) advising the customer to raise an issue for the encountered problem.

